## 5. Practical Advice and Best Practices

### Establish a Validation Checklist

Before deploying any Codex-generated code, verify:

- [ ] All unit tests pass with comprehensive coverage
- [ ] Integration tests pass (if applicable)
- [ ] Linting reports no errors
- [ ] Type checking passes (if using TypeScript/mypy)
- [ ] Code follows project style guidelines
- [ ] No security vulnerabilities introduced
- [ ] Performance characteristics are acceptable
- [ ] Documentation is updated (if required)

### Integrate Validation into Your Workflow

**Option 1: Pre-commit Hooks**

bash
# .husky/pre-commit (using husky)
npm run typecheck && npm run lint && npm run test


**Option 2: GitHub Actions Workflow**

